  "pages": [
    {
      "path": "/",
      "title": "digital-form-builder",
      "components": [
        {
          "type": "Para",
          "content": "`digital-form-builder` is a metadata-driven framework that builds top of a\r\nrobust, enterprise technical stack and the new gov.uk frontend Design System.",
          "options": {},
          "schema": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "Para",
          "content": "It allows form based gov.uk sites to be easily built with a graphical design tool.",
          "options": {},
          "schema": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "Para",
          "content": "A designer and developer from DDTS can use the tool alongside subject matter experts and service owners to quickly map efficient user journeys, ready to be tested in production ready code.",
          "options": {},
          "schema": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "InsetText",
          "content": "Using the graphical design tool, users can build sites from a toolkit of common GDS patterns that includes Pages, Sections and Navigation elements along with Components like Text Fields, Radios Buttons, Checkboxes and Date Fields.",
          "options": {},
          "schema": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "Para",
          "content": "The framework is <a href=\"/split\">flexible<a/>. It is capable of handling a number of different scenarios where form based page are required. E.g. collecting data in a transactional service or checking if a service is suitable for an end user.",
          "options": {},
          "schema": {}
        }
      ],
      "next": [
        {
          "path": "/benefits"
        }
      ],
      "section": "demo"
    },
    {
      "path": "/benefits",
      "components": [
        {
          "type": "Para",
          "content": "<ul class=\"govuk-list govuk-list--bullet\">\r\n  <li>Data quality is assured though data processing and validation rules.</li>\r\n  <li>Designers and subject matter experts can <b>collaborate</b> during the design process, creating\r\noptimised user journeys and intuitive content with clear visuals that are easy to work with\r\nand understand.</li>\r\n  <li>Reduces the amount of bespoke development required in both low volume and short\r\nprocess services.</li>\r\n<li>The framework works as a plugin to an established and proven tech stack. This not only gives\r\na robustness but also means that bespoke code can be run, <b>side by side</b> within the same site.</li>\r\n<li>The code produced is GDS compliant and production ready, eliminating the duplication of\r\neffort from prototypes to build.</li>\r\n</ul>",
          "options": {},
          "schema": {}
        }
      ],
      "section": "demo",
      "title": "Benefits",
